# Gemini CLI Command Conversion Template
# TAD v2.1 - Convert Claude Code commands to Gemini CLI TOML format

## Source Format
- Location: `.claude/commands/{command-name}.md`
- Format: Markdown

## Target Format
- Location: `.gemini/commands/{command-name}.toml`
- Format: TOML

## Conversion Rules

### 1. File Naming
- Source: `tad-alex.md`
- Target: `tad-alex.toml` (keep hyphen, change extension)

### 2. TOML Structure
```toml
description = "{one-line description from first heading}"

prompt = """
{full markdown content}

## Context
@{GEMINI.md}
@{.tad/skills/README.md}

## User Arguments
{{args}}

## Evidence Output
Generate evidence at: .tad/evidence/reviews/
"""
```

### 3. Placeholder Conversion
| Claude | Gemini |
|--------|--------|
| `$ARGUMENTS` | `{{args}}` |
| `{args}` | `{{args}}` |
| File reference | `@{path/to/file}` |
| Shell command | `!{command}` |

### 4. Skill References
- Change: "call subagent `code-reviewer`"
- To: "read skill from `.tad/skills/code-review/SKILL.md`"

### 5. Context Injection
Always add these context references:
```toml
@{GEMINI.md}
@{.tad/skills/README.md}
```

## Example Conversion

### Source (`.claude/commands/tad-gate.md`)
```markdown
# TAD Gate Command

Execute quality gate verification.

## Gates
- Gate 1: Requirements
- Gate 2: Design
...
```

### Target (`.gemini/commands/tad-gate.toml`)
```toml
description = "TAD: TAD Gate Command"

prompt = """
# TAD Gate Command

Execute quality gate verification.

## Gates
- Gate 1: Requirements
- Gate 2: Design
...

## Context
@{GEMINI.md}
@{.tad/skills/README.md}

## User Arguments
{{args}}

## Evidence Output
Generate evidence at: .tad/evidence/reviews/
"""
```

## Namespacing (Optional)

For namespaced commands, use directory structure:
- `.gemini/commands/tad/alex.toml` → `/tad:alex`
- `.gemini/commands/tad/blake.toml` → `/tad:blake`
